<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 7:32PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Wilkes
and western Yadkin Counties through 815 PM EDT...
At 731 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Windy Gap, or 8 miles southeast of North Wilkesboro, moving east at
20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
North Wilkesboro...
Jonesville...
Boonville...
Ronda...
Windy Gap...
Buck Shoals...
and Brooks Crossroads.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Seek shelter inside a building.</instruction>
